  "time_ut": 1659872502,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "MBSL \u0d86\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dab\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2 \u0d86\u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca SEC \u0dc4\u0dcf CSE \u0db6\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Request to SEC and CSE authorities from MBSL Margin Debt Investors",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Investors who have invested money in listed companies by obtaining margin loans through the margin loan department of Merchant Bank of Sri Lanka & Finance PLC (MBSL - MERCHANT BANK OF SRI LANKA & FINANCE PLC), a licensed bank in Sri Lanka and listed in the Colombo Stock Exchange. Those investors say that they are currently facing a severe injustice and difficulty.",
        "They point out that it is unfair that the MBSL company, which owns its shares bought through that loan, is ready to sell those shares at a low value in the Colombo Stock Exchange tomorrow (08th).",
        "In this regard, the concerned margin loan department of MBSL has informed the related stock broking companies as well as all the shareholders through an e-mail message recently.",
        "Accordingly, those investors have submitted requests to the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) and the Colombo Stock Exchange (CSE), which is the regulator of the Colombo Stock Exchange, to intervene for the immediate suspension of this share sale planned to be carried out by the MBSL company.",
        "Commenting on this, one of the investors said, \"Hundreds of people who invested in the Colombo Stock Exchange by taking this marginal credit facility of MBSL have been affected by now. Because they have taken a huge risk and invested their money and paid interest for the related loans. But in the last season, the stock market suffered a severe retreat, so they did not get as much profit as they expected. Now, as these investors are selling their shares at a low price, they are even more helpless.\" It is said.",
        "According to her, it is said that some people have committed suicide due to family problems.",
        "\"Due to the bad economic situation in the country throughout the last period, the prices of our shares went down. But now the economy is improving and the transactions in the Colombo Stock Exchange are progressing successfully. Therefore, we request that we be given the opportunity to sell these shares at the right price for another two months.\"",
        "According to the reports, MBSL is ready to sell these shares with the aim of winding down the operations of its margin loan department. Thus, the possibility of selling these shares is also mentioned in the agreement between the company and the Colombo Stock Exchange.",
        "However, the investors have requested the Securities and Exchange Commission and the Colombo Stock Exchange to consider the bad economic situation in the country in the last period and think humanely about these investors.",
        "Commenting on this, another investor said, \"Last year, we used to get these marginal loans and buy shares at 15% interest. After that it increased to 20%. With the beginning of this August, it has been made 25%. We came by paying such high interest. At times we made profits. At that time MBSL had to settle our debt. But they didn't. We think that is a trick. But now, when the economy is improving, we do not understand why they are selling shares at such a low price. This is frankly a case of unprofessionalism.\u201d It is also said."
      ],
